    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: ROCKWELL WABCO 4 CHANNEL - OPERATION - ATC</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ATC</title>
        <para>The ABS has an optional Automatic Traction Control (ATC). It helps move vehicles on slippery surfaces and
            reduces drive wheel overspin. The ATC works automatically in two different ways:
        </para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>If a drive wheel starts to spin, ATC brakes that wheel and transfers engine torque to the wheels
                    with better traction.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>If all wheels spin, ATC reduces engine torque to provide improved traction.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
